After 100 days of lockdown, the effects of the restrictions are taking its toll on South Africans. Many have mixed feelings while some are traumatised. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - After 100 days of lockdown, the effects of the restrictions are taking its toll on South Africans. Many have mixed feelings while some are traumatised. For some, 100 days of restrictions have pushed them to the edge. READ: Day 100 of lockdown: Nurse describes fight against COVID-19 Others are learning to adapt, trying making peace with the new normal. The lockdown’s effects are clearly wide-ranging. It will take time to understand exactly what psychological damage the restrictions have inflicted on the nation, especially as the end is not yet in sight. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.